---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';

const frontmatter = {
  title: "Portfolio Website Overview",
  description: "An in-depth overview of my fully functional Astro cybersecurity portfolio website.",
  pubDate: "September 20, 2025"
};
---

<MainLayout title={frontmatter.title} description={frontmatter.description}>
  <article class="post-content">

    <header class="post-header bubble">
      <h1>{frontmatter.title}</h1>
      <p class="post-date">{frontmatter.pubDate}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="bubble">
      <p>
        I am excited to share a detailed overview of my personal cybersecurity portfolio website.  
        The site is built using <a href="https://astro.build/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>, 
        a modern static site generator, and is designed to showcase my technical skills, projects, 
        experience, and professional journey. Below, I outline the key features, structure, and functionality of the website.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="bubble">
      <h2>Website Structure</h2>

      <h3>1. Hero Section</h3>
      <p>
        Introduces me with a professional headshot, name, and tagline summarizing my experience and objectives.  
        Call-to-action buttons allow visitors to download my resume or navigate to the contact page.
      </p>
      <ul class="inline-list">
        <li>Responsive design for desktop and mobile</li>
        <li>Clear, concise introduction with visual emphasis</li>
        <li>Easy access to resume and contact links</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>2. Featured Skills</h3>
      <p>
        Highlights core technical competencies with **pill-shaped tags**:
      </p>
      <ul class="inline-list">
        <li>Security Tools: InsightIDR, ZScaler, Mimecast</li>
        <li>Digital Forensics</li>
        <li>Threat Detection</li>
        <li>Networking: CCNA knowledge</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>3. Recent Write-ups</h3>
      <p>
        Blog-style section with posts and descriptions:
      </p>
      <ul class="inline-list">
        <li>How to Build a Cybersecurity Homelab</li>
        <li>Understanding SIEM Tools</li>
        <li>Digital Forensics Best Practices</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="bubble">
      <h2>Terminal Feature</h2>
      <p>
        An embedded interactive terminal allows visitors to explore the portfolio in a <strong>text-based interface</strong>.
      </p>
      <ul class="inline-list">
        <li>Access via toggle button in header</li>
        <li>Commands: <code>whoami</code>, <code>ls</code>, <code>cat [filename]</code>, <code>date</code>, <code>gui</code>, <code>help</code>, <code>clear</code></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="bubble">
      <h2>Additional Pages</h2>
      <p>The site includes these main sections:</p>
      <ul class="inline-list">
        <li>About — Personal & professional background</li>
        <li>Skills — In-depth technical skills</li>
        <li>Experience — Internship & work history</li>
        <li>Homelab — Cybersecurity lab overview</li>
        <li>Certifications — Professional qualifications</li>
        <li>Projects — Completed portfolio projects</li>
        <li>Blog — Research, challenges, CTF write-ups</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="bubble">
      <h2>Design and Usability</h2>
      <ul class="inline-list">
        <li>Responsive design for all screen sizes</li>
        <li>Glassmorphism & subtle radial backgrounds</li>
        <li>Interactive hover effects on buttons and posts</li>
        <li>Accessible semantic HTML and keyboard navigation</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="bubble">
      <h2>Conclusion</h2>
      <p>
        The portfolio website is a polished, interactive showcase of my cybersecurity skills, professional experience, and projects.  
        With a GUI, terminal, and clear hierarchy, visitors can explore my expertise in multiple ways.
      </p>
    </section>

  </article>
</MainLayout>

<style>
.post-content {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 2rem auto;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 2rem;
}

.bubble {
  background: var(--glass-bg);
  backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  border-radius: 2rem;
  border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  padding: 2rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
  box-shadow: 0 8px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
}

.post-header h1 {
  color: var(--accent-color);
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
}

.post-date {
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: #aab2bb;
}

h2 {
  color: var(--accent-color);
  font-size: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

h3 {
  color: var(--text-color);
  font-size: 1.4rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

p, li {
  color: var(--text-color);
  font-size: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.inline-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding-left: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.5rem;
}

.inline-list li::before {
  content: "• ";
  color: var(--accent-color);
  display: inline-block;
  width: 1em;
}

a {
  color: var(--accent-color);
  text-decoration: underline;
}

code {
  background-color: rgba(88, 166, 255, 0.1);
  padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
  border-radius: 0.25rem;
  font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
}

@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .post-content {
    padding: 1rem;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
  .bubble {
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
  h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.6rem; }
  h3 { font-size: 1.2rem; }
}
</style>
